<h2>Building Page Templates with Claude Code</h2>
<p>The template is the foundation of every programmatic SEO campaign. A well-built template produces pages that are structurally identical but content-unique.</p>
<h3>Template Architecture</h3>
<p>Every programmatic page template needs 5 components:</p>
<ol>
<li><strong>URL pattern</strong> ,  <code>/[category]/[entity]</code> (e.g., <code>/integrations/slack-google-sheets</code>)</li>
<li><strong>Title formula</strong> ,  <code>[Entity A] + [Entity B] Integration | [Brand]</code></li>
<li><strong>Meta description formula</strong> ,  <code>Connect [A] to [B] in minutes. [Unique data point]. Updated [date].</code></li>
<li><strong>Content blocks</strong>. Introduction, features, how-to, data section, FAQ</li>
<li><strong>Schema template</strong>. JSON-LD with dynamic fields per page type</li>
</ol>
<h3>Example: Building a Template with Claude Code</h3>
<p>Here is how you instruct Claude Code to generate a page template for an Astro-based site:</p>
<pre><code>Create a page template at src/pages/integrations/[slug].astro that:
- Accepts props: toolA, toolB, features[], pricing, lastUpdated
- Generates a unique H1: &quot;[toolA] + [toolB] Integration Guide&quot;
- Includes a feature comparison table
- Adds FAQ schema with 4 dynamic questions
- Creates an internal link to /integrations/ index page
- Follows the writing rules in CLAUDE.md
</code></pre>
<p>Claude Code reads your existing site structure, matches the code style, and generates a production-ready template file.</p>
